{
  "texts": [
    "Hartley et al. 2019; Pashchenko et al. 2020).",
    "In the mid-infrared range, one needs to disentangle between different emission regions to derive flux ratios totally free of microlensing (Stalevski et al. 2012; Sluse et al. 2013).",
    "Rest-frame emission with λ > 11 µm is probably the least susceptible to microlensing (Sect. 2.9.4), but is observationally out of reach for quasars at z 2.",
    "When the source size gets too large, one should also account for finite size effects arising because the macro-magnification is not constant over the source profile.",
    "In some rare situations, the source may even cross a macro-caustic introducing more dramatic changes of flux ratios but generally accompanied by spatially resolved emission."
  ]
}